main event: A bright white unidentified object was sighted moving in a northeasterly direction over the Pacific Ocean on February 8, 1961.
interesting points: The object appeared similar to a first magnitude star,The sighting lasted for about 5 minutes,The object was tracked moving between two sets of coordinates,It was sighted at different time intervals,There was speculation that it could possibly be a satellite.
sighted object: a bright white object with the appearance of a star
witness description: observed by naval personnel aboard the USS John S McCain
